		<td><b>Emulating NOAC based plug-n-play games</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This might sound like a really bad idea at first, but since many of these plug-n-play game systems are based on NOACs, shouldn't it be possible to add support for the games to a NES emulator via new mappers.  That is, simply treat the games as if they were any other pirate multicart.  I realize that NOACs are slightly different than a real NES, but then again, emulators support some multi-carts that come packed with Famiclones.
<br />
<br />Commercial dev for the NES never stopped, if you consider NOAC dev to be NES dev.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


